1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,613
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,613 --> 00:00:03,036
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,346 --> 00:00:05,606
Seriously, after feeding me and all...

4
00:00:05,606 --> 00:00:07,241
Shaking blankets was the hard work
you were talking about?

5
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:08,709
Grab the other end.

6
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:13,200
There's this one scene in dramas
I find ridiculous.

7
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:16,083
A man and a woman
shake a blanket together,

8
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:19,400
and when she lets go,
she dramatically falls into his arms.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,321
Don't you think that's ridiculous?

10
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:24,600
Enough chatter. On three, shake it.

11
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,060
One, two, three.

12
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,700
What are you two doing?

13
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:08,502
We were shaking out the blanket,
and our feet got tangled.

14
00:01:08,936 --> 00:01:10,033
What are you doing? Get up.

15
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,033
Yes.

16
00:01:12,272 --> 00:01:13,273
You're back?

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Did you have lunch?

18
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:18,345
Yeah, the Team Manager made us pasta.

19
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:19,833
Pasta?

20
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:22,700
There wasn't much in the fridge.
How did you make it?

21
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:25,552
I just improvised
with what was in the fridge.

22
00:01:26,234 --> 00:01:27,688
I see. I'm going in.

23
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:29,640
Yes, ma'am.

24
00:01:32,666 --> 00:01:33,727
What's wrong with Mom?

25
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,700
Did something happen at the CEO's house?

26
00:01:36,433 --> 00:01:38,098
No, she's just tired.

27
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,468
- I'm heading in too.
- Okay.

28
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,233
Are you okay?

29
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,500
I'm sorry. I was just so flustered.

30
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,300
So you just let go of my hand?

31
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,300
How disloyal.

32
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,500
Why did you insist
on shaking the blanket together?

33
00:01:57,426 --> 00:01:59,600
Anyway, I think this blanket
needs to be washed again,

34
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,388
so let's call it a day.

35
00:02:01,824 --> 00:02:03,400
You wanted to do more cleaning?

36
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:05,492
Cleaning finished!

37
00:02:07,852 --> 00:02:09,148
Anyway, what's that bike?

38
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,500
That's my brother's bike.

39
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,267
The brakes are broken,
and no one's ridden it in ages.

40
00:02:15,636 --> 00:02:17,771
I think it'll work if I fix it up a bit.

41
00:02:19,026 --> 00:02:20,574
Do you even know how to ride a bike?

42
00:02:20,733 --> 00:02:22,109
Seriously?

43
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,977
Just because I always ride on the back
of your scooter,

44
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:25,233
you thought I couldn't ride a bike?

45
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,052
Today must've been hard for you.

46
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:34,900
It's just...

47
00:02:35,055 --> 00:02:37,057
Why did it have to be that woman?

48
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,533
Did something happen between you two?

49
00:02:40,899 --> 00:02:43,066
Not exactly bad, but you saw her earlier.

50
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,166
With my personality, do you think
it'd be easy to put up with that?

51
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,303
Just let bygones be bygones
and get along from now on.

52
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:51,800
I guess I have no choice.

53
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,733
But it won't be easy for you either.

54
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:56,677
The husband and wife are exactly alike.

55
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:00,247
As an assistant, you have to put up
with all kinds of things.

56
00:03:00,247 --> 00:03:02,149
I'm just doing my job.

57
00:03:02,149 --> 00:03:03,200
What is there to put up with?

58
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:04,985
Don't worry about me.

59
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:08,688
But how did their son
turn out nothing like them?

60
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:11,925
The grandparents are such good people too.

61
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:14,795
Not every child
turns out like their parents.

62
00:03:15,533 --> 00:03:17,998
Anyway, who did they find...

63
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,267
that has the whole family in chaos?

64
00:03:21,546 --> 00:03:23,746
- Right?
- The CEO's mother...

65
00:03:24,252 --> 00:03:25,572
When she came in earlier,

66
00:03:26,053 --> 00:03:28,709
her face had gone completely pale.

67
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,979
What are you talking about?
Madam had a daughter?

68
00:03:34,233 --> 00:03:35,549
Besides Min Ho's dad,

69
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:38,151
did the Chairman and Madam
have another child?

70
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:40,133
Don't tell me Madam...

71
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,900
had another child...

72
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:44,758
before marrying the Chairman?

73
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,433
Why are you so curious?

74
00:03:47,266 --> 00:03:48,562
Mind your own business.

75
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:51,000
Are you really
going to keep being like this?

76
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,100
What exactly are you hiding?

77
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:55,300
What is it that I don't know?

78
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,833
Hey, Seo Gwon Sik!

79
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:02,833
You scared me.

80
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,100
Mom.

81
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,916
What now? What is it this time?

82
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,551
Seriously,

83
00:04:12,239 --> 00:04:14,939
even living with a stone statue
wouldn't be this frustrating.

84
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:21,600
You've already lived with Dad
for over 30 years.

85
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,231
Shouldn't you be used to it by now?

86
00:04:26,233 --> 00:04:28,235
Let me take this opportunity...

87
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:30,904
to relieve your stress.

88
00:04:33,219 --> 00:04:34,219
Ta-da.

89
00:04:34,506 --> 00:04:35,976
I got the contract deposit.

90
00:04:36,966 --> 00:04:37,966
What?

91
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:43,283
My goodness!

92
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,118
Why are you getting so shocked?

93
00:04:45,706 --> 00:04:49,200
The deposit is only 5,000 dollars?

94
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,591
"Only?"

95
00:04:57,633 --> 00:04:59,499
- Are you okay?
- It's so nice and cool.

96
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,769
It's nice.

97
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:05,000
Faster!

98
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:06,800
Nice!

99
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,200
The brakes...

100
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:27,233
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I think I'm okay.

101
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:29,496
- What about you, Team Manager?
- Yeah, I'm okay too.

102
00:05:30,526 --> 00:05:33,100
But why? I definitely fixed it.

103
00:05:34,533 --> 00:05:35,600
What a liar.

104
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,305
You said you were still looking
for something you can't do.

105
00:05:38,305 --> 00:05:40,040
We could've gotten seriously hurt.

106
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,233
What happened?

107
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,311
Wait, I'll fix it again.

108
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,600
I'm thirsty.

109
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:48,300
You fix it.
I'll go buy something to drink.

110
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,300
Okay.

111
00:05:56,053 --> 00:05:57,053
Did you fall?

112
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,033
Are you hurt? Let me see.

113
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,700
Are you okay?

114
00:06:06,093 --> 00:06:07,093
Want some ice cream?

115
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:10,833
Here.

116
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,717
Be careful on your way.

117
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:53,179
What should we do?
There's only one ice cream.

118
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:54,980
Here.

119
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:00,000
You don't like ice cream?

120
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,000
What?

121
00:07:01,386 --> 00:07:02,622
No, it's not that.

122
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:05,100
Thanks. Sit down.

123
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,433
Let's share it.

124
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:09,195
What? How do we share that?

125
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,233
Like this.

126
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,467
There, how's that?

127
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:16,800
I got too much.

128
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,204
It's fine.

129
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,600
It's good.

130
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,800
Why are you suddenly taking pictures?

131
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,254
I wasn't taking pictures of you.

132
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:35,933
The flowers over there were pretty.

133
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,325
You're so full of yourself.

134
00:07:38,592 --> 00:07:40,393
No, I'm not!

135
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,700
It's good.

136
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:49,900
It really is.

137
00:08:01,273 --> 00:08:02,273
Seung Ri.

138
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,300
There's someone I like.

139
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:07,520
Who is that person?

140
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:09,189
Whoever it is, one thing's certain.

141
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,033
In my heart,

142
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:14,427
there's no place for you
other than as a friend.

143
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:16,700
So...

144
00:08:17,753 --> 00:08:18,786
please let go...

145
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,533
of your feelings for me, Seung Ri.

146
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:39,433
Come in.

147
00:08:43,023 --> 00:08:46,000
I emailed you the first report
on the sports facilities analysis.

148
00:08:46,346 --> 00:08:48,829
Already? Good work.

149
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:53,700
Aren't you hungry?

150
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,670
Come to think of it, I skipped lunch.

151
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:01,095
Are you hungry? Then let's eat...

152
00:09:01,095 --> 00:09:03,577
Want to grab a drink instead?

153
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,913
What? A drink?

154
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,533
Did you know my first sketch
started in this neighborhood?

155
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:15,800
Really?

156
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:19,125
It's not easy
finding a neighborhood like this in Seoul.

157
00:09:19,659 --> 00:09:21,661
Everywhere else is packed
with apartment buildings.

158
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,333
But when you talked
about the alleys around here,

159
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,634
that's when I made up my mind.

160
00:09:29,433 --> 00:09:32,600
There's something fun
about walking through these alleys.

161
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:37,610
When you talked about the trails
in our retirement community,

162
00:09:37,806 --> 00:09:39,412
it reminded me of the alleys
in my neighborhood.

163
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,700
That's why working on it
felt even more exciting.

164
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,533
Even if I'm having a rough day elsewhere,

165
00:09:47,533 --> 00:09:49,055
the moment I step into this neighborhood,

166
00:09:50,179 --> 00:09:51,725
I just feel at ease somehow.

167
00:09:53,106 --> 00:09:55,128
I thought, "I want to live
in a place like this someday."

168
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,897
Then from that moment on...

169
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,133
Yeah, so don't try to kick me out.

170
00:10:01,968 --> 00:10:04,137
It's not like I want to kick you out.

171
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:08,333
Honestly,
I'm a little worried about Manager Seo.

172
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:13,200
Because I know how she feels about you.

173
00:10:14,259 --> 00:10:17,383
I think I know what you're worried about,
but you don't need to be.

174
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,354
This may sound strange, but Manager Seo...

175
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:24,300
is really like a younger sister to me.

176
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,400
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, want to try that?

177
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,600
Okay.

178
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,433
Hey, don't step on the lines.

179
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,150
Of course I won't.

180
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,097
It's out.

181
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,768
You have to place it carefully.

182
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,876
With your left foot.

183
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,514
Now then...

184
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:30,500
- Here I go.
- Five.

185
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,092
It touched the line!

186
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:34,527
It definitely touched the line.

187
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:35,800
It clearly touched the line.

188
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:46,406
I seriously doubted my ears earlier.

189
00:11:46,786 --> 00:11:49,653
Manager Seo asking me out
for drinks first?

190
00:11:52,906 --> 00:11:54,781
Drink slowly. You haven't eaten yet.

191
00:11:56,126 --> 00:11:57,126
Seo Seung Ri.

192
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,600
Are you worried about me right now?

193
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:01,688
I was just craving a drink.

194
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:03,000
Don't read into it.

195
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,825
Anyway, I'm in such a good mood right now.

196
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,794
Right, Ms. Cho Eun Ae's house is nearby.

197
00:12:08,794 --> 00:12:09,799
Should I call her out?

198
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,200
No.

199
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,966
Eun Ae's probably not home right now.

200
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:14,900
Really?

201
00:12:16,007 --> 00:12:17,304
You sure have sharp ears.

202
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,240
Why would we call her when she's probably
with the Team Manager at his place?

203
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:24,477
We must've heard wrong.

204
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:26,646
Maybe he just had the TV on.

205
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,400
The Team Manager's place?

206
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,583
Do they know something?

207
00:12:33,300 --> 00:12:35,000
That guy renting Eun Ae's room...

208
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,290
- Isn't he the Team Manager?
- Grandma, taste this for me.

209
00:12:38,926 --> 00:12:41,033
Do you have a problem with me?

210
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:42,500
I'm going to get indigestion at this rate.

211
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:44,700
Seo Seung Ri!

212
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:49,435
When are you ever going to look at me?

213
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:53,500
Why can't you see me?

214
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,600
Look at me.

215
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,176
What, am I invisible or something?

216
00:12:57,733 --> 00:12:58,933
Keep it down.

217
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:00,580
Why are you acting like this
at a restaurant?

218
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:02,613
That unrequited love of yours.

219
00:13:02,613 --> 00:13:04,380
Aren't you tired of it yet?

220
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:06,119
You don't need...

221
00:13:06,527 --> 00:13:08,660
to go through that.
I can go through it alone!

222
00:13:08,986 --> 00:13:10,986
If you keep this up, I'll leave first.

223
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,427
How long are you going
to keep being like this?

224
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:17,300
How long are you going
to treat me like I'm invisible?

225
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:18,665
Just how long?

226
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:21,468
If you don't get up now,
I'm leaving you here.

227
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:24,233
The check, please.

228
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:25,438
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

229
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,041
Are you really leaving me here?

230
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,500
Thank you. Please come again.

231
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:32,178
She's really leaving.

232
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,283
Thanks for the meal.

233
00:13:39,013 --> 00:13:40,053
I'll come again next time.

234
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:47,533
You waited instead of leaving.

235
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,633
You can walk properly, right?

236
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,100
I'll call a taxi.

237
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:53,533
Talk to me for a minute.

238
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,369
You seem drunk. Another time.

239
00:13:57,933 --> 00:13:59,000
The taxi's here.

240
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Seung Ri!

241
00:14:08,026 --> 00:14:10,249
That motorcycle's coming in fast.

242
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:13,133
My goodness.

243
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:15,700
Who's that, being all lovey-dovey
in front of someone's house?

244
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:18,733
Let's hurry up and go.

245
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,100
- Hurry.
- Okay.

246
00:14:50,379 --> 00:14:51,379
Seung Ri.

247
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,700
I'm okay with being hurt myself,

248
00:14:59,293 --> 00:15:01,193
but I can't bear
to see you hurting anymore.

249
00:15:02,979 --> 00:15:04,979
Please, stop this, okay?

250
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:37,900
I'm sorry.

251
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,706
I must've gotten too drunk.

252
00:15:42,966 --> 00:15:43,966
I'm sorry, Seung Ri.

253
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,400
Let's just go.

254
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:09,300
How's it been living at our house
for a few days?

255
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,633
I'm very comfortable and happy here.

256
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,473
Really?

257
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:15,041
Today, the Team Manager...

258
00:16:15,233 --> 00:16:17,300
cleaned the entire house.

259
00:16:18,153 --> 00:16:19,153
What?

260
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,147
Why would you do that?

261
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:26,200
No wonder the whole house was sparkling.

262
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:29,100
It was nothing.
I was bored, so I just vacuumed a little.

263
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:30,100
It was no big deal.

264
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:31,947
I helped too, you know.

265
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:34,733
By the way...

266
00:16:35,226 --> 00:16:37,559
I asked for 300 dollars for meal expenses,

267
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,999
so why did you send 500 dollars?

268
00:16:40,533 --> 00:16:43,300
You can barely eat for under ten dollars
at restaurants,

269
00:16:43,300 --> 00:16:45,905
and I'm eating two meals a day here.
I couldn't do that.

270
00:16:45,905 --> 00:16:47,440
Even so...

271
00:16:48,074 --> 00:16:49,759
Mom's making a decent profit here.

272
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:54,633
Here, this is a gift for both of you.

273
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:57,100
What? A gift for us?

274
00:16:57,517 --> 00:16:59,100
I got my contract deposit today.

275
00:16:59,546 --> 00:17:01,220
I was going to send it by bank transfer,

276
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:05,758
but I thought giving it in an envelope
would show my sincerity better.

277
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:08,100
Why would you give us
your contract deposit money?

278
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,264
Keep it and save it for your future.

279
00:17:11,579 --> 00:17:14,066
Yeah, save this money up...

280
00:17:14,066 --> 00:17:16,936
for when you get married someday...

281
00:17:16,936 --> 00:17:18,833
or move out on your own.

282
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:21,600
But make sure you keep paying
your living expenses regularly.

283
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,000
Of course I'll keep pitching in for that.

284
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:27,100
I'm sorry for disappointing you both,

285
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,833
but this means you don't have to worry
about me anymore, so please accept it.

286
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,133
Cho Eun Nim.

287
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:34,153
- I'm actually a little touched.
- It's too early to be touched.

288
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,123
I'm heading up first.
I'm behind on my serialization.

289
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:40,893
Okay, don't stay up too late.
Get some sleep.

290
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,429
Thank you. We'll use it well.

291
00:17:44,119 --> 00:17:46,365
I don't know
if we should really accept this.

292
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,033
- Of course you should.
- Hey!

293
00:17:50,033 --> 00:17:52,939
You worked so hard
to put her through med school!

294
00:17:52,939 --> 00:17:55,600
- Take it.
- I really can't...

295
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,600
Right.

296
00:17:58,439 --> 00:18:00,913
Is there someone
your grandma is looking for?

297
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:02,915
Sorry? Someone she's looking for?

298
00:18:03,046 --> 00:18:05,985
Your whole family was in an uproar today
because someone had been found.

299
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,300
You didn't know?

300
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,956
No, I didn't really know.

301
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,903
Grandma, it's me.

302
00:18:24,133 --> 00:18:25,138
Gyeol!

303
00:18:25,453 --> 00:18:27,740
I was just about to call you.

304
00:18:29,499 --> 00:18:30,643
Is everything okay?

305
00:18:31,746 --> 00:18:33,212
Of course. Everything's fine.

306
00:18:34,205 --> 00:18:35,881
Tell me where you moved to.

307
00:18:36,306 --> 00:18:38,217
I'll make you some side dishes.

308
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,386
Don't worry about me.

309
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:43,656
The family here makes sure
I eat two meals a day.

310
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:47,460
Really?
How did you find a place like that?

311
00:18:48,526 --> 00:18:49,762
I just got lucky.

312
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,564
How's Grandpa doing?

313
00:18:53,146 --> 00:18:56,636
He hasn't gotten any worse,
so don't worry too much.

314
00:18:56,636 --> 00:18:58,400
If you're curious
about your grandpa's condition,

315
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,272
come see for yourself, you punk.

316
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,477
Please tell him
I'll definitely visit sometime next week.

317
00:19:05,273 --> 00:19:06,306
Grandma...

318
00:19:06,866 --> 00:19:09,916
About the person you're looking for...

319
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:13,386
Never mind. I'll see you next week.

320
00:19:15,167 --> 00:19:17,823
Okay. Then come as soon as you can.

321
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:20,033
Is he coming?

322
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:38,933
Father.

323
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,180
I moved out.

324
00:19:42,966 --> 00:19:45,017
I feel sorry to Grandpa and Grandma,

325
00:19:46,033 --> 00:19:47,620
but they understood too.

326
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,000
It's only been a few days
since I moved into this house,

327
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:53,100
but it's strange.

328
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:56,896
It feels like...

329
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,131
I've finally come home for real.

330
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:04,036
This place is actually that kid's house.

331
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,133
Ever since I moved into this house,
I've been smiling a lot.

332
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:12,144
I eat well and sleep well too.

333
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:16,315
Is it okay for me to be like this?

334
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:22,300
Am I really allowed to be this happy?

335
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,076
Are you ready?

336
00:20:44,560 --> 00:20:46,379
Yes, let's go.

337
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,885
I have a feeling...

338
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,221
she'd wear the necklace too.

339
00:20:56,339 --> 00:20:59,325
That way,
we'll recognize each other right away.

340
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,600
Alright, let's go.

341
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,929
Yes, let's go.

342
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:14,633
It's raining a lot today.

343
00:21:15,212 --> 00:21:16,786
Are you dressed warmly enough, Chairman?

344
00:21:16,786 --> 00:21:18,577
Yes, I'm fine.

345
00:21:19,652 --> 00:21:21,847
But where are you going?

346
00:21:22,633 --> 00:21:24,150
Why do you need to know?

347
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,020
Mother, Father, can I come with you too?

348
00:21:28,593 --> 00:21:29,956
Why would you come?

349
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:32,800
I'm worried someone might pretend
to be your daughter...

350
00:21:33,006 --> 00:21:36,362
after hearing the Chairman of Kangsu Group
is searching for her.

351
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,732
Are you going to keep speaking carelessly?

352
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:41,767
I'm sorry.

353
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:45,337
Let's go, Chairman, Madam.

354
00:21:57,133 --> 00:21:58,300
Honey.

355
00:21:58,300 --> 00:22:00,719
They just left. What do we do?

356
00:22:01,353 --> 00:22:03,122
What if it's really her?

357
00:22:03,122 --> 00:22:05,100
Crystal, no way.

358
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,325
I don't think it's her.

359
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,327
Don't you know
the power of positive thinking?

360
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:11,931
If we desperately believe it's not her,
then it won't be.

361
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:14,967
Think about it.

362
00:22:15,299 --> 00:22:18,599
If she were that easy to find,
they would've found her years ago.

363
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:20,539
Seriously...

364
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,542
You scared me.

365
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:25,678
Mr. Cho, don't you know how to knock?

366
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:28,000
I did knock.

367
00:22:30,226 --> 00:22:31,517
These are the approval documents, sir.

368
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:39,233
Leave them and go.

369
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,600
I'm going to review them carefully,
so leave.

370
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,800
But you need to approve these now...

371
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:47,100
for them to get
to the Chairman's office today.

372
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,000
Really?

373
00:22:58,712 --> 00:22:59,712
Are you finished?

374
00:22:59,912 --> 00:23:01,412
Yeah, here.

375
00:23:03,079 --> 00:23:04,149
You know...

376
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:07,486
Mr. Cho, as you heard before,

377
00:23:08,026 --> 00:23:10,622
my parents are looking for someone.

378
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,300
And Gwon Sik...

379
00:23:13,253 --> 00:23:15,861
I mean, Mr. Seo is holding
onto all the information.

380
00:23:16,279 --> 00:23:17,379
So if you could somehow...

381
00:23:17,866 --> 00:23:20,166
sweet-talk Mr. Seo...

382
00:23:20,433 --> 00:23:22,933
into sharing it...

383
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,472
Would Mr. Seo share information with me...

384
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,407
that he hasn't shared with anyone
until now?

385
00:23:28,733 --> 00:23:30,409
Yeah, I guess not. All right.

386
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:33,400
- You can go now.
- Then excuse me.

387
00:23:37,012 --> 00:23:38,651
This is driving me crazy.

388
00:23:39,152 --> 00:23:42,719
Why do I completely shrink up
whenever he's around?

389
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,524
I'm the boss, and he's my assistant.

390
00:23:46,026 --> 00:23:47,193
There's absolutely no reason
for me to be like this...

391
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:50,663
And yet I am. This is driving me insane.

392
00:23:51,130 --> 00:23:53,632
(Hanbi Police Station)

393
00:24:02,633 --> 00:24:04,643
She's arrived and is waiting.

394
00:24:05,133 --> 00:24:07,246
Really? Let's go in.

395
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:09,733
Honey.

396
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:13,500
I...

397
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:16,455
I'll go in alone.

398
00:24:16,958 --> 00:24:19,199
Why? I'll come too.

399
00:24:19,199 --> 00:24:20,200
No.

400
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,500
Today...

401
00:24:25,026 --> 00:24:27,032
I want to meet her alone.

402
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:32,471
All right. Then I'll wait here.

403
00:24:33,012 --> 00:24:36,342
Once the DNA test starts today,

404
00:24:36,342 --> 00:24:38,184
they said the results should come
within a few days.

405
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,079
Don't get too anxious.

406
00:24:41,979 --> 00:24:45,296
Okay. I'll go in.

407
00:24:53,926 --> 00:24:56,829
(Visitation Room)

408
00:25:55,822 --> 00:25:56,822
Please sit.

409
00:25:57,933 --> 00:25:58,933
Okay.

410
00:26:08,146 --> 00:26:10,269
I heard both your age and name...

411
00:26:11,713 --> 00:26:13,813
were changed.

412
00:26:15,379 --> 00:26:19,178
Do you remember anything
from when you were little?

413
00:26:21,139 --> 00:26:23,015
I got severe meningitis...

414
00:26:23,417 --> 00:26:25,417
before being adopted by a French family,

415
00:26:26,220 --> 00:26:27,820
and I lost all my memories.

416
00:26:28,233 --> 00:26:29,588
Goodness...

417
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:37,700
Excuse me, but...

418
00:26:38,933 --> 00:26:40,299
Could I see your calf?

419
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:42,433
Sorry?

420
00:26:42,727 --> 00:26:45,438
There's something
I absolutely need to check.

421
00:26:57,433 --> 00:27:00,052
Why is it raining
like it's the monsoon season already?

422
00:27:03,606 --> 00:27:06,992
Every time it rains,
my calf aches so much.

423
00:28:21,466 --> 00:28:22,834
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
